@s-alexey we didn't really thought this through yet I'm afraid. 

One idea that immediately pops to mind is to enhance tokens with their POS tag. Hence, when doing classification one could distinguish between play used as a verb versus play used as a noun. This could be done by appending the tag after the token (e.g. `play_VB`). We could store this directly into `corpus.tokens`, though this is not very nice from the code design point of view, but it would instantly work for classification. 

Further POS tags could also be used for token filtering (but we would probably need an other widget for that). It might be interesting to compare different writing styles by observing how adjectives and verbs are used. For example, I could take a book, filter out everything but adjectives and observe this in a WordCloud.

@nikicc Just to clarify how to tackle adding new attribute for Corpus Viewer. Did we agree on introducing a new **string** attribute which simply joins all tagged tokens? E.g.:
`pos_tags = "cat_NN, jumps_JJ, over_STH......."`
And then one can view all pos-tagged tokens for each document.

